cs.DB, cs.DC, cs.OS, cs.DS, cs.PL 

This paper is primarily focused on improving the concurrency control protocol for database management systems (DBMSs) in multicore systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DB (Databases). The paper also discusses the system architecture and recovery mechanism, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.OS (Operating Systems) and cs.DS (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The use of dependency graphs and parallelism also indicates that it could be relevant to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.PL (Programming Languages).
